msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:116
msgid ""
"To keep the source for the documentation consistent when many different "
"people are editing it, please follow these style conventions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Acronyms"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:121
msgid ""
"Acronyms should be defined the first time they appear in a document, as in: "
"\"Network Time Protocol (NTP)\". After the acronym has been defined, use the "
"acronym alone unless it makes more sense contextually to use the whole "
"term. Acronyms are usually defined only once per chapter or per document."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:123
msgid "All acronyms should be enclosed using the ` character."
msgstr ""

